WEBVTT

00:02.084 --> 00:05.463
KATIE: The opening ceremony of the
Bee Day festival was awesome!

00:05.463 --> 00:08.048
It's my favorite part of
Bee Awareness Day.

00:08.048 --> 00:09.425
My favorite part
is the B-flat

00:09.425 --> 00:12.345
with an F-sharp bass
at the end of the song.

00:12.345 --> 00:13.805
What?
It's tradition.

00:13.805 --> 00:15.473
Okay, girls,
festivities are over.

00:15.473 --> 00:18.100
Let's focus on getting
our Beekeeping Patches.

00:18.100 --> 00:20.311
It's the only patch that we've
ever tried to get and failed.

00:20.353 --> 00:22.438
Remember last year?

00:22.438 --> 00:25.441
You promised to never flash
back on that ever again!

00:25.441 --> 00:26.984
Right! Right.
You're right.

00:26.984 --> 00:28.986
But still, if we
don't succeed today

00:28.986 --> 00:30.571
the "two strikes and
you're out" rule kicks in.

00:30.571 --> 00:32.323
Which means this spot
will stay empty

00:32.365 --> 00:35.117
on all of our
sashes forever!

00:35.117 --> 00:37.328
Chill out, Isabella.
We've got this.

00:37.328 --> 00:39.247
Ready, girls?

00:39.247 --> 00:40.832
ALL: They're gone!

00:40.832 --> 00:42.250
Gone?

00:42.250 --> 00:45.461
Fighting flash-forward
to potential catastrophe.

00:45.461 --> 00:47.088
Hey, where's Pinky?

00:51.342 --> 00:52.510
(BARKING)

00:55.012 --> 00:56.514
<i>ACRONYM: Good afternoon,
Agent Pinky!</i>

00:56.514 --> 01:00.351
<i>I see you've token our new
handbag conveyor system.</i>

01:00.393 --> 01:02.395
<i>Carla here has intel that
Poofenplotz has been</i>

01:02.395 --> 01:05.355
<i>hatching up some sort of
bee-related evil scheme.</i>

01:05.355 --> 01:08.484
<i>Yes, it seems that
Poofenplotz is researching</i>

01:08.484 --> 01:10.361
<i>the use of royal jelly
in the bee community.</i>

01:10.403 --> 01:12.154
<i>(BEEPING)
Oh, there's your coffee.</i>

01:12.154 --> 01:16.033
<i>She comes from on entire
family of unpaid interns.</i>

01:16.033 --> 01:17.535
<i>Anyway, see if
there is anything</i>

01:17.535 --> 01:19.370
<i>to Carla's research,
Agent Pinky.</i>

01:19.412 --> 01:20.997
<i>Admiral Acronym out.</i>

01:24.417 --> 01:26.127
Gah! We've gotta
find those bees

01:26.127 --> 01:28.170
before the sun
goes down, but how?

01:28.170 --> 01:30.047
In the guidelines for
the Beekeeping Patch,

01:30.047 --> 01:31.382
